    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Works created with ink and diluted ink applied with a brush, usually on paper. They are variously classified as paintings or as drawings. Examples of highly developed ink wash paintings are found in Chinese and Japanese tradition. Usage may overlap with "pen and wash drawings," which however involve drawing with a pen, not only brush.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000031001/Oxford Dictionary of Art (1988)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093897/Metropolitan Museum of Art [online] (2001-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Werken die zijn gemaakt met inkt en verdunde inkt, aangebracht met een penseel, meestal op papier. Ze worden soms als tekeningen, soms als schilderingen geclassificeerd. Voorbeelden van sterk uitgewerkte gewassen inktschilderingen worden aangetroffen in de Chinese en de Japanse traditie. Het gebruik kan overlappen met 'gewassen pentekeningen', maar hierbij wordt ook een pen gebruikt, niet alleen een penseel.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Trabalhos criados com tinta de escrever e com a mesma tinta diluída aplicada com um pincel, geralmente sobre papel. Eles podem ser classificados como pinturas ou desenhos. Exemplos dessas pinturas altamente elaboradas são encontradas nas tradições chinesa e japonesa. O uso pode se sobrepor com "desenhos com caneta e tinta aguada", que envolvem o desenho com uma caneta e não somente com pincel.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000110648/Portuguese Translation Intern Project (2020-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
